body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

Yosys seems to be unable to parse the following input;

```verilog
//K-input Look-Up Table
module LUT_K #(
    //The Look-up Table size (number of inputs)
    parameter K, 

    //The lut mask.  
    //Left-most (MSB) bit corresponds to all inputs logic one. 
    //Defaults to always false.
    parameter LUT_MASK={2**K{1'b0}} 
) (
    input [K-1:0] in,
    output out
);

    specify
        (in *> out) = "";
    endspecify

    assign out = LUT_MASK[in];

endmodule
```

It produces the following error;
```
1. Executing Verilog-2005 frontend.
Parsing Verilog input from `./vtr_flow/primitives.v' to AST representation.
./vtr_flow/primitives.v:128: ERROR: syntax error, unexpected ',', expecting '='
```

Is this even valid Verilog? SystemVerilog? ModelSim seems to successfully parse it (doesn't mean it's valid however :-)

